No, theſe three are one, ſays Mr. Dean; one by mutual Conſciouſneſs. I anſwer, beſides that this amounts to no more than to an Unity of Accord, which (as has been ſaid) is not the Unity that the Church and Fathers ever held, and which we have ſeen the Council of Sardis avowed to be the Catholick Faith ever taught, received and delivered down, (
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ) one Subſtance, or an Unity of Subſtance; beſides this, I ſay, three thouſand Minds or Spirits may be as well conceived mutually conſcious, as three; and ſo we may defend Polytheiſm, or maintain all the Gods of the Heathen to have been but one.
